<reference id="Application_Server_Resources_74" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title><ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> Domain</title>
    <refbody>
        <section>
            <p>The following sections give an overview of the resources which must be provided for the <ph
                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> domain (<codeph>bes-domain</codeph>) on the application server. The resources are defined in:</p>
            <p>
                <codeblock>domains\bes-domain\installer\resources-template.xml</codeblock>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Data Source</title>
            <p>A JDBC data source with a corresponding connection pool is required for the relational databases where <ph
                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> stores its data. </p>
            <table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth=""/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth=""/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Name</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>BSSDS</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Class name</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>org.postgresql.xa.PGXADataSource</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Resource type</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>javax.sql.XADataSource</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Database schema</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="co21">As distributed with <ph
                                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>JMS Queues</title>
            <p>The following JMS queues and corresponding connection factories are required for asynchronous processing:</p>
            <p>
                <ol>
                    <li><b>Trigger queue: </b><p>Queue name: <codeph>jms/bss/triggerQueue</codeph></p><p>Connection factory name: <codeph>jms/bss/triggerQueueFactoryConPool</codeph>
                        </p></li>
                    <li><b>Task queue: </b><p>Queue name: <codeph>jms/bss/taskQueue</codeph></p><p>Connection factory name: <codeph>jms/bss/taskQueueFactoryConPool</codeph>
                        </p></li>
                    <li><b>Indexer queue: </b><p>Queue name: <codeph>jms/bss/indexerQueue</codeph></p><p>Connection factory name: <codeph>jms/bss/indexerQueueFactoryConPool</codeph>
                        </p></li>
                    <li><b>Master indexer queue:</b><p>Queue name: <codeph>jms/bss/masterIndexerQueue</codeph></p><p>Connection factory name: <codeph>jms/bss/masterIndexerQueueFactoryConPool</codeph>
                        </p></li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>All queues and connection factories mentioned above use the following settings: </p>
            <p>
                <table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth=""/>
                        <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth=""/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1">
                                    <b>Initial and minimum pool size</b>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <codeph>1</codeph> connection </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1">
                                    <b>Maximum pool size </b>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <codeph>250</codeph> connections </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><b>Idle timeout</b></entry>
                                <entry><codeph>600</codeph> seconds</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><b>On any failure</b></entry>
                                <entry><codeph>Close all connections</codeph></entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><b>Transaction support</b></entry>
                                <entry><codeph>XATransaction</codeph></entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><b>Connection validation</b></entry>
                                <entry><codeph>Required</codeph></entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1">
                                    <b>UserName</b>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <codeph>jmsuser</codeph>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1">
                                    <b>Password</b>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="co21">
                                    <codeph>jmsuser</codeph>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </p>
            <p>The master indexer queue / connection factory requires the following additional setting: </p>
            <p>
                <table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth=""/>
                        <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth=""/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1">
                                    <b>AddressList</b>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2">
                                    <codeph>&lt;master-indexer-host-name>:&lt;port></codeph>, where <codeph>port</codeph> is the port number of the search indexer application domain. <p>Default: <codeph>8476</codeph></p></entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </p>
            <p>
                <note>Make sure that the JMS service type is set to LOCAL. In a default GlassFish configuration it is set to EMBEDDED. When using the installation scripts for installing OSCM, the service type is set to LOCAL automatically.<p>If you need to change the service type manually, you can run, for example the following command: </p><p><codeph>asadmin set server.jms-service.type=LOCAL</codeph>
                    </p></note>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Java Mail Session</title>
            <p>A Java Mail Session is required for the application server to automatically send emails in case of specific user actions. </p>
            <table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth=""/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth=""/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>JNDI Name</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>mail/BSSMail</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Store Protocol</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>imap</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Transport Protocol</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>smtp</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>mail-smtp-auth</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>false</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>mail-user</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>saas</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>mail-smtp-port</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>25</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>mail-smtp-password</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>password</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1"><b>mail-smtp-connectiontimeout</b></entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>30000</codeph></entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <p>The settings are retrieved from the <codeph>glassfish.properties</codeph> file located in <codeph>&lt;install_pack_dir>/domains/bes_domain</codeph> when running the installation scripts. The <b>JNDI Name</b>, <b>Store Protocol</b>, and <b>Transport Protocol</b> are mandatory and must not be changed. </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title> Realm</title>
            <p><ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> comes with a custom realm implementation in the <codeph>oscm-security.jar</codeph> archive (located in <codeph>&lt;install_pack_dir>/domains/bes_domain/lib</codeph>), which is included in the installation package. The realm must be configured as follows: </p>
            <table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colnum="1" colname="col1" colwidth=""/>
                    <colspec colnum="2" colname="col2" colwidth=""/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Name</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>bss-realm</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>JAAS context</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>bssRealm</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <b>Implementation class</b>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <codeph>org.oscm.security.ADMRealm</codeph>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Certificate Realm</title>
            <p>The certificate realm of the application server must be assigned the role <codeph>CLIENTCERT</codeph>.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Default File Encoding</title>
            <p>Ensure that the default file encoding of the application server's Java virtual machine is UTF-8. This can be achieved by setting the <codeph>file.encoding</codeph> system property to <codeph>UTF8</codeph>.</p>
        </section>
    </refbody>
